article.headline: New Hampshire 68, Vermont 65
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Mike Christensen scored 24 points and Tyrece Gibbs 19 to lead New Hampshire to a 68-65 victory over Vermont on Thursday night, snapping an 8-game losing streak against the Catamounts as it finished its regular season. Trailing 46-39 midway through the second half, the Wildcats (9-19, 6-10 America East) went on a 14-1 run. Mike Trimboli's 3-pointer pulled Vermont within 53-52, but Tyrone Conley hit a trey for New Hampshire and James Valladares' dunk gave the Wildcats a 66-60 lead with 23 seconds left. Marqus Blakely hit two free throws for Vermont and Valladares added one for New Hampshire before Colin McIntosh hit a 3-pointer for Vermont's last points with 3 seconds to go. Christiansen scored the last point on a free throw, and New Hampshire intercepted Vermont's long in-bound pass as time expired. Blakely and Trimboli each had 16 points for Vermont (14-14, 8-7).
